One card from each set is a great idea . . . in theory. In reality it's a colossal pain in the ass to do well, and even if you do it does using Watchwolf as your Rav card or some random fucking common from Scourge or whatever as the representative of that set really count? I mean, yeah, you can say you had one card from each set, but you're just checking that box. There's just no way you can meet the goal of having one memorable card that makes people think of the set in question while still having it hit your EV mark and draftability mark.
